OL,6,FThe apology says the murder has not
OL,7,Fbeen the subject of a full and
OL,8,Feffective investigation in accordance
OL,9,Fwith article two of the European
OL,10,FConvention on Human Rights, and
OL,11,Faccepts a conclusion by the former
OL,12,FHistorical Enquiries Team that police
OL,13,Fcould have taken steps to provide
OL,14,Fpatrolling in the area after
OL,15,Fsuspicious activity was reported.
OL,17,F"That dedicated action may have
OL,18,Fprevented Paul's murder," the apology
OL,19,Fstates.
