OL,4,Capology over failings
OL,6,FThe UK government took a legal effort
OL,7,Fto the Supreme Court to prevent
OL,8,Fcoroner Louisa Fee from disclosing a
OL,9,Fsummary, or gist, of the evidence in a
OL,10,Fsensitive security force file
OL,11,Ffollowing an inquest into Mr
OL,12,FThompson's death. A ruling has not yet
OL,13,Fbeen made.
OL,15,FMr Thompson welcomed the apology from
OL,16,FMr Boutcher, and said he hopes to see
OL,17,Fthe judgment from the Supreme Court
OL,18,Fsoon.
